primary.$description: Used for key headings across pages.

primary_on-brand.$description: Applied to headings placed on solid brand-colored areas, often seen in themed sections like CTAs.

secondary.$description: Used for Button & Input label and section titles.

secondary_hover.$description: The visual style for secondary text when hovered over.

secondary_on-brand.$description: Designed for secondary-level content on solid brand-colored sections, such as CTA banners.

tertiary.$description: Best suited for body content and supporting information.

quaternary.$description: Used for subtle, low-contrast content like footer labels or muted annotations.

tertiary_on-brand.$description: Applied to supportive text placed on branded backgrounds, typically in promotional areas.

quaternary_on-brand.$description: Used in low-emphasis areas over brand-colored sections, like footers.

white.$description: Always remains white, regardless of light or dark mode settings.

placeholder_subtle.$description: A less prominent placeholder style, good for contexts like verification inputs.

brand-primary.$description: Used for prominent headings in branded sections, like pricing cards.

brand-secondary.$description: Suitable for accent content highlights, or subheadings (e.g. in blog cards).

brand-tertiary_hover.$description: Variant used when hovering over branded interactive text, such as buttons.

brand-tertiary.$description: Designed for such as button labels or less emphasized numeric values (e.g. in metrics).

error.$description: Color used to indicate error states, especially in form inputs & buttons

warning.$description: Used to flag warnings or cautionary messages.

disabled.$description: Applied to input fields or buttons.

brand-disabled.$description: Suitable for accent content such as button labels, highlights, or subheadings (e.g. in blog cards).

error_hover.$description: Variant used when hovering over branded interactive text, such as buttons.

tertiary_on-brand-alt.$description: Designed for such as button labels.

brand-secondary_alt.$description: Suitable for accent content highlights, or subheadings (e.g. in blog cards).

primary.$description: Used for outlines in components like input fields, button groups, and checkbox.

secondary.$description: Used for typical UI elements like file uploaders, tables, and content dividers.

tertiary.$description: Useful for very subtle dividers and borders such as line and bar chart axis dividers.

disabled.$description: Used on elements like disabled buttons, input fields and checkboxes.

secondary_alt.$description: An alternative to secondary border that uses alpha transparency. This is used exclusively for floating menus such as input dropdowns and notifications to create sharper bottom border.

brand.$description: Useful for active states in components such as active input fields.

error.$description: Useful for error states in components such as buttons, input fields and file uploaders.

warning.$description: Default warning state semantic border color.

success.$description: Default success state semantic border color.

brand-disabled.$description: Useful for disabled borders such as disabled buttons.

error-disabled.$description: Useful for disabled borders such as disabled buttons.

error_subtle.$description: Useful for error states in components such as buttons.

brand_subtle.$description: Useful for active states in components such as buttons.

brand_alt.$description: Useful for active states alternatively with border-brand.

tertiary_alt.$description: An alternative to secondary border that uses alpha transparency. This is used exclusively for floating menus such as input dropdowns and notifications to create sharper bottom border.

mockup.$description: Useful for borders such as mockup.

primary.$description: Highest contrast non-text foreground elements such as icons.

secondary.$description: Medium contrast non-text foreground elements such as icons in buttons

tertiary.$description: Low contrast non-text foreground elements help icons, and icons used in input fields.

secondary_hover.$description: Secondary foreground elements when in hover state.

white.$description: Foreground elements that are always white, regardless of the mode.

disabled.$description: Disabled non-text foreground such as icons in disabled button group buttons, input dropdown menu items, disabled active checkboxes and tag checkboxes.

tertiary_hover.$description: Tertiary foreground elements when in hover state.

brand-primary.$description: Primary brand color non-text foreground elements such as brand button icons and progress bars.

brand-secondary.$description: Secondary brand color non-text foreground elements such as accents and arrows in website design.

error.$description: Default error for non-text foreground elements, especially in form inputs & buttons.

warning.$description: Default warning for non-text foreground elements.

success.$description: Default success for non-text foreground elements.

brand-primary_on-brand-alt.$description: Primary brand color non-text foreground elements such as brand button icons.

brand-disabled.$description: Disabled non-text foreground such as icons in disabled button group buttons.

error-disabled.$description: Disabled non-text foreground such as icons in disabled button group buttons.

brand-primary_hover.$description: Hover state color non-text foreground elements such as brand button icons.

error_hover.$description: Hover state color non-text foreground elements such as button icons.

brand-secondary_alt.$description: Alternative color non-text foreground elements such as accents and arrows in website design.

brand-primary_alt.$description: Non-text foreground elements that switches to gray when in dark mode such as active horizontal tabs.

primary.$description: The primary background color (white) used across all layouts and components.

primary_hover.$description: Hover state background color for components with white backgrounds (e.g. input dropdown menu items).

primary-solid.$description: The primary dark background color useful for components such as tooltips and Text editor tooltips & overlay components such as modals.

secondary.$description: The secondary background color used to create contrast against white backgrounds, such as website section backgrounds.

secondary_hover.$description: Secondary background hover color. Useful for hover states for navigation items and date pickers.

tertiary.$description: The tertiary background color used such as toggles, sliders and progress bars & Miscellaneous Icons.

disabled.$description: Default disabled background color for components such as disabled primary buttons, input fields, checkboxes and toggles.

brand-primary.$description: The primary brand background color for components such as buttons.

brand-secondary.$description: The secondary brand background color for Miscellaneous Icons.

brand-solid.$description: Useful for components such as buttons, toggles and messages.

brand-section.$description: Used for website sections such as CTA sections and testimonial sections.

brand-solid_hover.$description: Hover state useful for components such as buttons, toggles.

error-primary.$description: Primary error state background color for components such as buttons.

error-secondary.$description: Secondary error state background color for Miscellaneous Icons.

error-solid.$description: Background color for components such as buttons, Miscellaneous Icons, and metric items.

error-solid_hover.$description: Hover state background color for components such as buttons.

warning-primary.$description: Primary warning state background color for components.

warning-secondary.$description: Secondary warning state background color for Miscellaneous Icons.

warning-solid.$description: Background color for components such as Miscellaneous Icons.

success-primary.$description: Primary success state background color for components.

success-secondary.$description: Secondary success state background color for Miscellaneous Icons.

success-solid.$description: Background color for components such as Miscellaneous Icons.

secondary-solid.$description: The secondary dark background color for Miscellaneous Icons.

brand-disabled.$description: Default disabled background color for components such as disabled primary buttons.

error-disabled.$description: Default disabled background color for components such as disabled buttons.

brand-solid_alt.$description: Useful for components such as buttons.

white.$description: Background elements that are always white, regardless of the mode.

active.$description: Active state components such as (e.g. menu items in input fields).
